    "revise": "You are the FIGURE REVISER (Opus) for \"The LLM Stack\". Chapter: content/02-transformer/08-architecture-variants.md\nThe chapter's core intuitions: The attention MASK is the single defining characteristic of each family: bidirectional (encoder), lower-triangular causal (decoder), and the hybrid prefix-LM block. The mask decides what information can flow where.; Encoder-only is bidirectional and therefore great for understanding but structurally incapable of autoregressive generation (predicting token t+1 would require attending to t+1 itself).; Encoder-decoder pairs a bidirectional encoder with a causal decoder joined by cross-attention (decoder queries, encoder keys/values), at the cost of two stacks and a cross-attention KV cache.; Decoder-only factorizes p(x) autoregressively with a causal mask and is trained to predict every next token, so training extracts a loss signal at EVERY position.\n\nReview each of these figures (the ones this chapter just drew/edited):\n  archvar-encoder-only-stack, archvar-encoder-decoder-crossattn\n\nFor EACH: render and SEE it \u2014 `python3 scripts/preview_fig.py <NAME> --theme both` from /local-ssd/pk669/programming/llm-stack-textbook,\nthen view /tmp/figpreview/<NAME>.light.png and .dark.png. Judge strictly:\n  - Does it actually BUILD INTUITION for its concept (not just decorate)? Is it correct vs the chapter?\n  - Theme-safe (no hardcoded primary color; readable in BOTH light and dark)?\n  - Nothing clipped by the viewBox; no illegible overlaps; no tofu glyphs (ASCII only in the SVG)?\n  - Marker present in the chapter exactly once; figcaption has a bold lead + takeaway?\nIf a figure has ANY problem, FIX it: Edit /local-ssd/pk669/programming/llm-stack-textbook/figures/<NAME>.html (and re-render to confirm), or\nfix a missing/duplicate marker in the chapter. Re-verify after fixing.\n\nSet verdict per figure: good / fixed / still-broken / missing. `passed` = every figure good-or-fixed\nAND present. Return the structured object."
