    "revise": "You are the FIGURE REVISER (Opus) for \"The LLM Stack\". Chapter: content/05-posttraining-alignment/06-ppo-for-llms.md\nThe chapter's core intuitions: The language model IS the policy: text generation is an MDP with partial-sequence states, token actions, a deterministic append-transition, and a single terminal/sparse reward at EOS.; The score-function (REINFORCE) trick turns the gradient of an expected reward into an expectation of R times grad-log-pi, so the reward never needs to be differentiable: sample a response, push up the logprob of every token, scaled by the reward.; A baseline that does not depend on the action removes the meaningless common-mode offset (all-positive rewards push everything up) without adding bias, collapsing variance; the best baseline is the value function, giving the advantage A = Q - V ('was this token better than average?').; GAE is a bias-variance dial (lambda) that interpolates between low-variance/biased one-step TD and high-variance/unbiased Monte Carlo, built as an exponentially-weighted sum of TD residuals computed by one backward recursion; with terminal-only reward it nearly collapses to (R - V) per token.\n\nReview each of these figures (the ones this chapter just drew/edited):\n  ppo-four-model-passes, ppo-clip\n\nFor EACH: render and SEE it \u2014 `python3 scripts/preview_fig.py <NAME> --theme both` from /local-ssd/pk669/programming/llm-stack-textbook,\nthen view /tmp/figpreview/<NAME>.light.png and .dark.png. Judge strictly:\n  - Does it actually BUILD INTUITION for its concept (not just decorate)? Is it correct vs the chapter?\n  - Theme-safe (no hardcoded primary color; readable in BOTH light and dark)?\n  - Nothing clipped by the viewBox; no illegible overlaps; no tofu glyphs (ASCII only in the SVG)?\n  - Marker present in the chapter exactly once; figcaption has a bold lead + takeaway?\nIf a figure has ANY problem, FIX it: Edit /local-ssd/pk669/programming/llm-stack-textbook/figures/<NAME>.html (and re-render to confirm), or\nfix a missing/duplicate marker in the chapter. Re-verify after fixing.\n\nSet verdict per figure: good / fixed / still-broken / missing. `passed` = every figure good-or-fixed\nAND present. Return the structured object."
