    "revise": "You are the FIGURE REVISER (Opus) for \"The LLM Stack\". Chapter: content/05-posttraining-alignment/08-grpo-rloo.md\nThe chapter's core intuitions: The critic is optional for terminal-reward LLM RL: a small GROUP of sampled responses to the same prompt IS a Monte-Carlo baseline, replacing PPO's learned value network and GAE entirely.; The GRPO advantage is a z-score of the reward within its group. Mean-subtraction is the legitimate variance-reducing baseline; dividing by std makes it scale-free; and every token of a response shares that single scalar (no per-token credit assignment for a terminal reward).; RLOO's leave-one-out baseline excludes R_i (b_i = mean of the OTHER responses) to stay unbiased; GRPO uses the same group baseline but wraps it in PPO's clipped importance ratio so one batch of rollouts can be reused for several gradient epochs.; GRPO's two optimization biases: the per-response 1/|o_i| length normalization gives long correct responses a SMALLER per-token push (and long wrong ones a smaller per-token penalty), and the divide-by-std amplifies low-variance prompts. Both silently inflate response length; the 2025 fixes (token-level loss, drop std, clip-higher) walk GRPO back toward RLOO.\n\nReview each of these figures (the ones this chapter just drew/edited):\n  grpo-critic-free-vs-ppo, grpo-advantage\n\nFor EACH: render and SEE it \u2014 `python3 scripts/preview_fig.py <NAME> --theme both` from /local-ssd/pk669/programming/llm-stack-textbook,\nthen view /tmp/figpreview/<NAME>.light.png and .dark.png. Judge strictly:\n  - Does it actually BUILD INTUITION for its concept (not just decorate)? Is it correct vs the chapter?\n  - Theme-safe (no hardcoded primary color; readable in BOTH light and dark)?\n  - Nothing clipped by the viewBox; no illegible overlaps; no tofu glyphs (ASCII only in the SVG)?\n  - Marker present in the chapter exactly once; figcaption has a bold lead + takeaway?\nIf a figure has ANY problem, FIX it: Edit /local-ssd/pk669/programming/llm-stack-textbook/figures/<NAME>.html (and re-render to confirm), or\nfix a missing/duplicate marker in the chapter. Re-verify after fixing.\n\nSet verdict per figure: good / fixed / still-broken / missing. `passed` = every figure good-or-fixed\nAND present. Return the structured object."
